This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks related to facial keypoint detection, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques such as transfer learning and unsupervised learning, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of a pre-trained network and the development of a new dataset, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
